label: ACDCTerminal
comment: An electrical connection point (AC or DC) to a piece of conducting equipment. Terminals are connected at physical connection points called connectivity nodes.

label: ClearSimulationEvent
comment: Defines an event which clears another event such as ParemeterEvent or Fault.

label: DetailedModelDescriptor
comment: Describes different components of a detailed model.

label: DynamicsFunctionBlock
comment: Abstract parent class for all Dynamics function blocks.

label: EquipmentFault
comment: A fault applied at the terminal, external to the equipment. This class is not used to specify faults internal to the equipment.

label: Fault
comment: Abnormal condition causing current flow through conducting equipment, such as caused by equipment failure or short circuits from objects not typically modelled (for example, a tree falling on a line).

label: FaultCauseType
comment: Type of cause of the fault.

label: LineFault
comment: A fault that occurs on an AC line segment at some point along the length.

label: ParameterEvent
comment: Used to apply changes to particular parameter or signal. The parameter or signal could be any property from power flow part of the model or property/signal of standard, user defined or detailed model.

label: PowerFlowSettings
comment:
Provides information on power flow settings valid for the model they are assigned to.
The following attributes:
- staticVarCompensatorControlPriority, 
- switchedShuntControlPriority,
- transformerPhaseTapControlPriority, and
- transformerPhaseTapControlPriority 
 shall have different values in case they are enabled (i.e. value different than 0).

label: SignalConfiguration
comment: A configuration or a set of signals selected for recording during a simulation.

label: SignalDescriptor
comment: Describes the signals both internal signals that connect different functions or external signals.

label: SignalRecorder
comment: A recorder for a given signal.

label: SimulationEvents
comment: A configuration or a set of events executed during a simulation.

label: SimulationSettings
comment: Describes simulation settings necessary for a simulation.

label: Terminal
comment: An AC electrical connection point to a piece of conducting equipment. Terminals are connected at physical connection points called connectivity nodes.
